  <h2>Training Day vs. Rest Day Adjustments</h2>
  <p>Creatine should be taken daily regardless of training status, as the goal is sustained saturation of intramuscular phosphocreatine stores, not acute performance effects. Electrolyte needs are higher on training days due to sweat losses. On rest days, a maintenance electrolyte dose (roughly half the training day dose) supports recovery-phase protein synthesis and cellular hydration.</p>

  <h2>Session Length Considerations</h2>
  <p>For sessions under 60 minutes: standard daily electrolyte intake with creatine is sufficient. For sessions 60 to 90 minutes: add 300 to 400 milligrams of sodium during the session. For sessions over 90 minutes: 300 to 600 milligrams of sodium per hour, with potassium and magnesium proportionally adjusted. These are the ranges supported in the ACSM guidelines and the 2011 sports nutrition review.</p>

